5.4 Commercial Buyout Option
Where a Cooperation Result is initially owned by Party A alone or jointly owned, Party B may seek a negotiated buyout of Party A's relevant interest. Unless the Parties agree otherwise in writing, the reference commercial terms shall be as follows:
one-time patent buyout fee: USD 36,000 per patent family;
running royalty option: USD 1.80 per commercialized product unit;
milestone payment: additional USD 18,000 upon cumulative sales exceeding 30,000 units within twenty-four (24) months after first commercial launch.
These figures are reference pricing only and shall not create an automatic transfer without a separate written assignment or license agreement.

7.1 Material Breach
A Party shall be deemed in material breach of this Agreement if it:
(a) assigns, licenses, discloses, or transfers a patent right in violation of Section 5.2;
(b) refuses without reasonable cause to cooperate in filing under Section 4.4;
(c) intentionally conceals inventorship or contribution evidence relevant to ownership determination under Section 3; or
(d) materially breaches any confidentiality, exclusivity, or IP cooperation obligation under the Main Contract in a manner that affects patent ownership or exploitation.
